    "Pathogens, including fungi, bacteria, and viruses, can devastate entire plant populations, leading to substantial economic losses and food shortages.",
    "Likewise, pests, ranging from insects to nematodes, have the potential to decimate crops, leading to decreased yields and quality.",
    "Food crops around the world face substantial yield reductions due to microbial diseases and pest infestations.",
    "These losses are significant, with rice experiencing an average loss of 30.3%, maize at 22.6%, wheat at 21.5%, soybeans at 21.4%, and potatoes at 17.2% (Savary et al., 2019).",
    "Plant diseases can be especially devastating, leading to yield reductions of up to 50% in specific regions, particularly impacting small-scale farmers and posing substantial economic challenges."
